-- Portugal Hotel Revenue Declines 0.8 Percent in August, INE Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-10-12T10:17:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-12/portugal-hotel-revenue-declines-0-8-percent-in-august-ine-says.html
Portugal ’s hotels recorded a 0.8
percent decline in revenue in August from the same month last
year as overnight stays by local tourists fell.  Revenue dropped to 297.9 million euros ($387 million) in
August, the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute said
today in an e-mailed statement. In the first eight months of the
year, revenue declined 2 percent to 1.3 billion euros.  Tourism represents about a tenth of Portugal’s gross
domestic product, according to the  Economy Ministry .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
